 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uquarasshadowscythe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Quaras Shadowscythe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 8:10:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4515.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Coldain Sawl 8??  Going to be implemented?</span><hr size=1> From the Dev Corner:<br>
<br>
There are 10 coldain quest rings.<br>
There are now 4 qeynos quest investigator badges.<br>
Unfortunately, there are still only 7 coldain quest shawls.<br>
The quest text following shawl 7 speaks of more shawls to come. Additionally, there is a quote floating around purported to be from the Verant employee in-the-know stating that there would be 10 coldain quest shawls.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately, I've also heard a rumor that the brilliant designer that made the ring and shawl quests was fired. I also see the shadows of Luclin over the horizon.<br>
<br>
So, I worry that you have decided to forego creation of further coldain prayer shawl quests.<br>
<br>
It has been a _LONG_ time now since the 7th shawl was added. Could you _please_ confirm that the 8th shawl is still slated for development? Hoping so, could you estimate when it might be live? Pre or post Luclin?<br>
<br>
Thank you,<br>
Flintnilf<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
quote:<br>
---------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Flintnilf,<br>
<br>
Firstly, I assure you the rumors of my termination have been greatly exaggerated. I'm still here and staying very busy helping to make Luclin the best expansion it can be.<br>
<br>
I regret that I was unable to complete the implementation of the final quests for the Coldain Shawl before Luclin production began. It's still my intention to implement the remaining segments, but my current workload has forced me to postpone its completion. I hope you'll feel the remaining portion was worth the wait.<br>
<br>
Steve Burke<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
<br>
I dunno about all of you, but I think it's better that Steve work on completing the quests when he's got more time to do it right. I can't express to you how much work this guy puts into making these things work. But it's a lot.<br>
<br>
Alan<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uqhue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Qhue</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 9:20:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4515.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> That was months ago</span><hr size=1> The posted bit from the Dev corner is about 6 months old now.   <br>
