<br>
I'm personally hoping for FT4 and 10% focus across the board on 10th shawl...note I said hoping, not expecting... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uwendolynkeplegrobal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wendolyn KeplegrobAL</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.wired-cafe.com/images/wendhead.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 10:57:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4515.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: That was months ago</span><hr size=1> Steve Burke designed the shawl quest.  He posted a while ago (fall 2001?) that he was busy with Luclin, and therefore had no time to add shawls 8, 9, and 10... but that once Luclin was underway he would get back to work on them.  However, given the current state of Luclin, I would imagine that's the farthest thing from his mind right now.  I could be (and hope I am) wrong though.  Shawl 8 will probably require 200 skill in begging, alcohol tolerance, and elder dragon with a 25 rare-drop sheet fold smithing check on the Ancient Needle of Timesink ^_^   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=morgrist>Morgrist</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/25/02 1:15:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4515.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> They've actually been good about fixing quests....</span><hr size=1> Someone is working their way through old broken quests (Blued 2H Hammer and Gnoll Slayer being notable recent fixes) and updating others (shaman cudgel being a good example).<br>
 <br>
Thus,I have faith in seeing more shawl quests in time.<br>
 <br>
-Morgrist<br>
